okcho_beach"],"enrichment_batch":"17d","enrichment_date":"2026-04-29","enrichment_kb_version":"1.26","enrichment_target_kb_version":"1.27","profile_version_pre":6,"profile_version_post":6,"schema_version":7,"patch_type":"polish_existing_pv6_to_a_grade","patch_target":"13 substantive stops across 4 tours; Batches 8/9 era authoring → A-grade pv=6 PASS (universal source-attribution gap closed; Seoul-day-trip-quartet pattern introduced)"},"itinerary_variants":[],"_publication":{"schema_version":"v4_canonical","last_modified":"2026-04-29","version_history":["v11","v12","v13","v14","v15","v17_batch9"],"fix_passes":{"v12":"P0+P1 — pickup_dropoff Schema A unification, routeFlowStops type-based, competing_products → internal slugs, anchor_poi_keys aligned","v13":"P1.5 — pickup_dropoff Schema A.2 → A.1; practicalAccordionItems / routePhases / seasonalVariations unified to V4 canonical (no Tailwind in data)","v14":"P2 — _publication uniform; duration formatting standardized; glanceItems Duration added where missing","v15":"P3 round 1 — SEO trim. seo.pageTitle rewritten to ≤65 chars (was 14/25 over 70); seo.metaDescription rewritten to ≤168 chars (was 25/25 over 170). primaryKeywords and ogImage unchanged. Hero/OG images, POI verification, review imports, and routePhases enrichment deferred to later P3 rounds.","v17_schema_unification":{"date":"2026-04-28","description":"Phase 1: Converted matching_profile scores from 1-5 int scale to 0-1 float scale to match the 3 Step 3 new tours. Mapping 1→0.20, 2→0.40, 3→0.60, 4→0.80, 5→1.00. Mechanical conversion preserves ordinal information; verified-fact recalibration happens in subsequent enhancement batches.","fields_converted":43,"fields_skipped":0,"fields_already_float":0},"v17_batch9_enhancement":{"date":"2026-04-29","description":"Batch 9 deep enhancement — Seoul-Seoraksan-Sokcho + Pocheon Sanjeong/Herb/Art Valley pair. Single-POI fixed-itinerary methodology (batches 1-5, 8 style). Both tours are SMALL_GROUP — formula different from batch 7/8 private tours. All substantive stops enhanced with 1,000+ char descriptions weaving verified facts. matching_profile recalibrated to verified-fact 0-1 float scores. Charter-format dimensions previously null: private_tour_fit set to 0.05 (definitionally not private); customizable_route_fit set to 0.1 (small-group fixed itinerary); flexibility_fit set to 0.3 (small-group bus, fixed pickup/drop). Tour-specific: history_culture_fit Seoraksan 0.5 (Sinheungsa 652 + Gwongeumseong 1253 + Tongildaebul 1997) / Pocheon 0.4 (1925 reservoir + quarry restoration). Seoraksan tour: unesco_fit 0.2 → 0.4 (UNESCO Biosphere Reserve since 1982, Korea''s only one); autumn_foliage_fit set to 1.0 (catalog-leading); mountain_fit set to 1.0 (catalog-leading); seasonal_fit 0.95. Pocheon tour: romantic_fit set to 0.85 (catalog-second-strongest after Nami tour 0.95); seasonal_fit 0.85; family_fit 0.8 → 0.85. 6 new POIs added to KB (v1.11 → v1.12): seoraksan_national_park, sokcho_tourist_fishery_market, sokcho_beach, sanjeong_lake, herb_island, pocheon_art_valley. KB POI count: 62 → 68.","_score_audit":{"_methodology":"0-1 float scale per Phase 1 standard. Both tours are SMALL_GROUP (not private) — formula different from Batch 7/8 private tours. Charter-format dimensions previously null on these tours: private_tour_fit set to 0.05 (definitionally not private); customizable_route_fit 0.1 (small-group fixed itinerary - no menu of routes); flexibility_fit 0.3 (small-group bus, fixed pickup/drop, fixed stops). history_culture_fit set per content: Seoraksan tour 0.5 (Sinheungsa Silla 652 + Gwongeumseong 1253 legend); Pocheon tour 0.4 (Sanjeong 1925 reservoir + Art Valley quarry-history). Time-weighted indoor_ratio re-computed per Fix 1 methodology using verified per-POI indoor_ratio_at_stop values.","deltas_applied":{"private_tour_fit":{"old":null,"new":0.05,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — both tours are small-group bus/coach tours, definitionally not private. Was unset (None)."},"customizable_route_fit":{"old":null,"new":0.1,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — small-group fixed itinerary; no route options. Was unset."},"flexibility_fit":{"old":null,"new":0.3,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — small-group format; fixed pickup/drop times, fixed stops, fixed pacing. Was unset. Lower than batch 7/8 private (0.6-0.8)."},"history_culture_fit":{"old":null,"new":0.5,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Sinheungsa Temple founded 652 (Silla) + Gwongeumseong Fortress 1253 Mongolian-invasion legend + Tongildaebul 1997 reunification monument. Substantial culture, but mountain nature dominates. 0.5 calibrated."},"unesco_fit":{"old":0.2,"new":0.4,"reasoning":"VERIFIED higher — Seoraksan IS a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve since August 1982 (Korea''s only one). NOT a World Heritage Site (only on tentative list). Calibrated up to 0.4 — Biosphere Reserve carries weight but isn''t the World Heritage gold standard."},"iconic_landmark_fit":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — Korea''s #1 most-loved national park, world''s largest seated bronze Buddha. Maintained at 1.0."},"first_time_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"Verified — strongest first-time mountain + East Sea single-day option. Slight upward to 0.85."},"walking_level":{"old":0.6,"new":0.65,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Seoraksan paths are paved at base (Sinheungsa, cable-car base) but Biseondae is 3 km walking; cable car eliminates the steep hike; Sokcho stops are flat. Time-weighted ~0.65."},"indoor_ratio":{"old":0.1,"new":0.15,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Fix 1 time-weighted: Seoul departure 15 × 1.0 (transit) = 15, Seoraksan 180 × 0.05 = 9, Sokcho Market 75 × 0.5 = 37.5, Sokcho Beach 75 × 0.0 = 0, Lunch 30 × 0.9 = 27, Return 150 × 1.0 = 150, transit-other 195 × 1.0 = 195. Total indoor 433.5 / 720 min = 0.60 with full transit; substantive only 73.5 / 360 = 0.20. Catalog value 0.15 (slight upward from prior 0.10 — better reflects market interior weight)."},"weather_sensitivity":{"old":1,"new":0.9,"reasoning":"Verified — Seoraksan cable car closes in high wind / heavy rain / fog (no view); Sokcho Beach is fully exposed; Sokcho Market is the only weather-protected fallback. Heavy-outdoor day. Slight markdown to 0.9 (very high but Sokcho Market provides partial fallback)."},"scenic_level":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — Korea''s most iconic mountain + East Sea coast. Maintained at 1.0."},"photo_level":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — Tongildaebul Buddha + cable-car panorama + East Sea + Sokcho Eye Ferris Wheel. Maintained at 1.0."},"nature_fit":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — Korea''s first UNESCO Biosphere Reserve. Maintained at 1.0."},"autumn_foliage_fit":{"old":null,"new":1,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Seoraksan autumn foliage (October-early November) is Korea''s most famous foliage destination, with cable-car-framed granite peaks. Was unset. Maximum 1.0."},"mountain_fit":{"old":null,"new":1,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Daecheongbong 1,708m (Korea''s 3rd highest), 30 peaks, Ulsanbawi granite formation. Catalog-leading mountain content. Was unset. Maximum 1.0."},"seasonal_fit":{"old":null,"new":0.95,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — autumn foliage peak Oct-Nov is the iconic season; spring azaleas + summer green + winter snow each have distinct appeals. Was unset. 0.95 calibrated."},"beach_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — Sokcho Beach is one of Korea''s representative East Sea beaches (75-min stop). Slight upward from 0.8 to 0.85 — beach is included but not the day''s centerpiece (Seoraksan is)."},"food_fit":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — Sokcho Tourist Fishery Market is Gangwon''s signature food market (dakgangjeong, squid sundae, abai sundae). Maintained at 1.0."},"small_group_fit":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — small-group coach format with driver-guide. Maintained at 1.0."},"bus_fit":{"old":1,"new":1,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — coach vehicle. Maintained at 1.0."},"premium_fit":{"old":0.4,"new":0.4,"reasoning":"Verified maintained — small-group coach with shared pickup is mid-tier value proposition. Maintained at 0.4."},"value_for_money_fit":{"old":0.8,"new":0.85,"reasoning":"Verified — 12-hour day covering UNESCO Biosphere mountain + signature market + East Sea beach at small-group pricing is strong value. Slight upward from 0.8 to 0.85."},"storytelling_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.75,"reasoning":"VERIFIED higher — Sinheungsa Silla founding (652 CE), Gwongeumseong 1253 Mongolian-invasion legend, Tongildaebul 1997 reunification monument, Sokcho Abai Village Korean War refugee heritage. Driver-guide narrative is rich. Calibrated up to 0.75."},"family_fit":{"old":0.6,"new":0.65,"reasoning":"VERIFIED — 12-hour day with optional steep hikes is moderate for families. Cable car + market + beach all family-friendly. Slight upward to 0.65."}}}}}}}'::jsonb
